transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Customer Service, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I have an account with you guys and you guys keep charging me and somehow it's on auto refill.

Speaker 1: And I did not, I don't want that. You guys just charged me right now $63 or something like that.

Speaker 2: And I just want to refund it. I don't want the prescription sent.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'm on your website right now. There's no way I can cancel it or alter it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you have to call in to do it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, well.

Speaker 1: What's your name and birthday? I'll do it.

Speaker 2: 12-24-1969.

Speaker 1: Okay. And then what's your name?

Speaker 2: Jack Rodriguez.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Jack. Give me a second.

Speaker 2: Okay, I altered it and I paused it, so you just have to call in to place an order.

Speaker 1: Or you could do it online, but I would suggest calling in so you don't run into it.

Speaker 2: So I can't cancel it altogether?

Speaker 1: Cancel what? Your account or?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Because if I paused it somehow, and I believe I paused it before, and somehow it just kept charging me, so.

Speaker 2: No, you have to call in and pause. You can't pause online.

Speaker 1: Can I cancel it?

Speaker 2: Yeah, let me go ahead and cancel this for you.

Speaker 1: The order that was from yesterday went out already, so when you receive it, you just have to send it back.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but when are you going to refund my money? Because I didn't ask for it to be sent out.

Speaker 1: Right, so.

Speaker 2: You guys sent it out automatically, so that's on you guys.

Speaker 1: When you place the order online.

Speaker 2: I just want my money refunded.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me talk.

Speaker 2: So once you place the order online, there was a box for you to uncheck.

Speaker 1: That's how it got on a monthly.

Speaker 2: Once you receive the package and the mail person scans the package back, it's going to automatically trigger the refund.

Speaker 1: That's how it works.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but I never signed for that.

Speaker 1: And a lot of times I'm not even home.

Speaker 2: Well, you don't have to be home to get it. You just have to return it back to the mailman or back to the post office.

Speaker 1: How do you do that?

Speaker 2: You drop it off or you hand it back to the mailman you don't want it?

Speaker 1: I ain't got time for all that. I'm a busy guy. I'm in and out of this house, and I'm not here a lot.

Speaker 2: That's what I'm saying. I don't have to deal with all that.

Speaker 1: Can you cancel my account completely?

Speaker 2: I did cancel your account.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: How do I make sure that my card's not going to be charged again?

Speaker 1: Can you send me some email confirmation?

Speaker 2: You should get a notification email once I select it to cancel out, but your entire account is canceled.

Speaker 1: Once you receive the packaging from the pharmacy, you just have to return to sender.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay. Have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right.
